'Mr. President, I am here to tell you we are not buying what you are selling in 2012.'

Love was born in Brooklyn, N.Y., raised in Connecticut and moved to Utah in 1997 where she married and converted to Mormonism.

Her parents arrived in the U.S. 39 years ago. Her father working several jobs to support the family.

In an interview with Fox news she said: 'I remember taking my dad to college with me on the first day of orientation and he looked at me very seriously, and he said, "Mia, your mother and I have done everything we could to get you here. We've worked hard. We've never taken a handout. You're not going to be a burden to society. You will give back,"'

